STATE OF NEW JERSEY, DEFENDENT IN ERROR, v. HUBERT CROMWELL, PLAINTIFF IN ERROR. Submitted March 22, 1923 Decided November 10, 1923.

Before Gummere, Chief Justice, and Justices Swayze and Trenchard.

For the plaintiff in error, Palmer & Powell. For the defendant in error, Jonathan H. Kelsey, prosecutor of the pleas. Per Curiam.

This case was argued with State v. Michalis, No. 9 of the same term. The only question presented here was disposed of adversely to the defendant in the opinion in State v. Michalis filed this day. See Advance Eeports.

The judgment will be affirmed, with costs.
